Mr. West:              -Called your company this afternoon and spoke to Debbie regarding the damages to our property. She was very courteous and patient and I appreciate her time.  However, it seems appropriate that we directly inform you of our concerns. In October, during the ongoing Country Club Road project in St. Charles,your employees accidentally graded the entire width of our property. That afternoon, Mr. Moore of St. Charles County Hwy. Dept., apologized and assured us that the soil would be replaced.(Per our January 13, 2005 settlement agreement with St. Charles County, our property was to remain at the 3:4 slope.)  We have already lost all of our shrubbery, a beautiful old tulip tree and countless other plants and had planned to do as much replanting as possible when the road project was completed. Our soil was beautiful and we could easily grow a variety of plants. We were willing to be patient about the soil replacement and felt that the situation would be rectified in the future as time allowed.  However, we were extremely disheartened to find that instead of replacing the soil, your company dumped layers of old ground asphalt and gravel along the sides and on top of our embankment, and that apparently, there are no plans to replace the soil. I have spoken with a representative from the DNR and an agronomist from the MU Ext. Center. Both stated that the land will now sustain little more than weeds. Ironically, some soil from our neighbors\' property was removed today during the sidewalk installation.  This beautiful soil is sitting in piles along the street to be used as fill elsewhere, while our embankment is now so hard and crusty with packed asphalt that I could barely even scratch the surface. Since we are off work during the holidays, we would like to bring this issue to a reasonable conclusion.  We have contacted the county several times and are simply asking for a resolution to this. We feel that this damage, left unabated, will destroy our privacy and devalue our property, and possibly affect our subdivision neighbors as well. We also contend that this is a violation of our 2005 agreement with the county as established in Circuit Court. We appreciate your time and attention in this matter.  Respectfully, Scott and Bets Yaeger      636-443-0674

Do you know what all governments; cities and local authorities will need in the next decades? Do you know how big business would be if only you could do it for them in the whole World? Now we offer 20%-50% business share of the company which is based on our patent, facilitating the prevention of traffic congestion in junctions. This patented innovation will be able to differentiate you from the ordinariness in the next 17 years. Due to the rapid increase of the number of vehicles, traffic congestion occurring on public roads – mostly at the junctions – represents an increasingly serious problem. Vehicles standing in congestion not only pollute the environment, but also increase the risk of accidents by the stress on drivers and the haste after getting out of the traffic jams. Our new traffic distribution system, called Vortexjunction can ensure a balanced speed and a non-stop traffic flow in an intersection even with more than half a million vehicles per one day like a spaghetti-type bridge system does, but with a lower construction cost and with much more advantages. The original concept of the VORTEX roundabout is that the special „vortex-like” lay-out of the lanes enables the vehicles to pass through the traffic distribution structure, maneuvering between the lanes in one direction from the outside towards the inside, which significantly reduces the risk of accidents and facilitates and accelerates a non-stop traveling. Vortexjunction is the optimal solution in suburban area in the crossing of more than two roads carrying heavy traffic. The configuration of the intersection is flexible, it can be fit for the actual conditions and be able to operate the traffic effectively and safely according to the changing conditions. In the World numerous existing but aging big multi-level bridge systems must be changed soon to this cheaper and more effective Vortexjunction, instead of the expensive reconstruction to the same style. And due to the Vortexjunction’s simple structure, the quick reconstruction of a busy junction would last for a shorter period. Many more intersections should also be changed soon to this brand new Vortexjunction, where a spaghetti-type bridge system would had been the only one existing solution for heavy traffic problems, but that was too expensive. And as cities and traffic keep growing in the whole World, hundreds of new intersections will be built also in our Vortexjunction style in the renewed districts worldwide. We strongly believe that Vortexjunction will lead to very significant savings from several macroeconomic points of view. Furthermore it’s understood thing that all governments are going to compensate the general economy crisis with more road making projects in the next years. And in addition our invention is really a common interest, because for billions of people Vortexjunction is going to mean a better traveling with time- and energy-saving every day, there would be less fuel usage, less air pollution and less transportation time for millions of cars monthly, and – as road safety aspect is also extremely important, – fewer accidents as well. It is also important that Vortexjunction with its simple circular shape and few one-level-passovers would be a very nice and preferred improvement in citizen’s environment. For many governments and a lot more local authorities of towns Vortexjunction is going to mean millions of dollars from cost-savings in construction, because the construction costs of Vortexjunction are lower than those of other solutions that would be equivalent from the aspect of and traffic control and have similar maximum traffic permeability. In addition they can get enormous money from the benefits of the gained territories in an inhabited area, because a wide open space in the middle-field of Vortexjunction would be available for any kind of business establishment to build in, so this saleable land property can reduce a lot from the total construction cost! Briefly this new VORTEX system is a brand new opportunity for all traffic engineers and city-planners to make more economic and society benefit! If you were an investor or a local road constructors, we offer NOW to be the one and only principal contractor or building contractor with us, who can build this Vortexjunction and get the leading role in the building industry locally or just participating of selling its licenses anywhere in the World in the next two decades. We intend to establish an incorporated company with a tenderable investor anywhere in the World. We put out our prior rights for claiming national patents as a non-cash capital contribution that worth 3 million USD. In the beginning we expect minimum that our partner should fund 600,000 USD capitals into this business for a 20% BUSINESS SHARE of this company. We intend to sell maximum 50% business share for 1,500,000 USD for providing the operating cost until the big success within 5 years. The structure is ready for construction in new building projects. So now we all together should manage this project according to our preliminary business plan or leading by your professional knowledge, demonstrate the idea on conferences, promote it to the industry and lobby for business opportunities worldwide, meanwhile more and more studies will convince everybody it is time for changing. Vortexjunction will come into general use everywhere in the World soon and it will mean more and more profits for us year by year and it will carry all before one! Saint Louis MO 63123  December 2008---February 2009  My Position------Operations Manager  As the Operations Manager I was responsible for all staffing of the warehouse and inside sales personnel.  Overseeing the daily processing of customer orders.  Responsible for managing and coordinating the purchase of goods and services for the company in a most  efficient and economical matter.  Expedite orders when required, following up on order progress and resolving any discrepancies.  Interview incoming sales representatives, and stay abreast of new changes in the industry or market.  Update vendor and customer files, checking invoices, and rebid contracts as needed.  Act as a liaison between the purchasing department and the general accounting department at our home office.  Obtain pricing, specifications, and sources of supplies for our budgeted projects.  Maintain and update product, service, vendor, and catalogue files.  Dispose of company assets which are no longer needed or are obsolete, including the processing of all associated  forms and paperwork.  Perform administrative functions, including transferring calls from the switchboard, filing, and greeting customers.  Proofread incoming orders for completeness, and to be error free.  Assist in faxing purchase orders and bid request.  Washington Tractor Company  Washington Missouri 63090  February 2007 --- October 2008  My Position------- Service Operations / Warehouse Manager  I was ultimately responsible for pro actively leading our Service Department and establishing budgets. Monitor the condition and inventory of all tools and maintenance equipment. Ensure the department meets all financial budgets and goals. Establish promotional service prices. Ensure the department adheres to all federal, state and local guidelines as well as company standards. Greet customers, scheduling service appointments, and write work orders for the equipment repair needs. Enter work orders into the system and input information on the repair order. Refer technicians to the equipment for diagnosis and testing to confirm source(s) of service repairs. Estimate the cost and time needed to do the repair. Handle customer complaints and maintain high customer satisfaction standards. Periodically check on the progress of the equipment during servicing, and update the work order as needed. Manage all warehouse functions, and insure we stay within the proper operating budgets while supporting our rental machinery with the parts and services that are required for operation. Close all work orders, and insure they are entered into our accounts receivable ledgers  Review P/L sheets and prepare figures for the owner to analyze.  Perform performance reviews on all branch employees, and recommend them for pay increases.  Maintain proper PM schedules for equipment maintenance and longevity.  I had direct interaction with our customers, sales department, parts department, and  our service department to coordinate all matters were addressed and followed through on.  Writing and selling service contracts, preventative maintenance contracts, and parts orders.  Doing 90 day inspections on all sold equipment to verify all numbers were properly filed for  warranty and if the customer needed to make contact with us from the field..  Sale of construction tools and machine attachments to the end users. (pumps, generators, jack  hammers, skid steers, rock drills).  Resolving customer conflicts and billing issues regarding our parts and service departments.  Deliver parts to the customers if they were in a down situation.  Perform under carriage inspections on all brands of machinery to keep the customer informed  of any issues they were unaware of, or any upcoming issues.  Quoting and securing any service work for our shop to perform.  Drive revenue from 13 Missouri counties, and directly service 1300 separate customers.  Conduct blade inspections for our quarry customers to insure bucket damages were not going to be an issue for them.  United Rentals Inc.  Saint Louis Missouri 63020  July 2003---February 2007  My Position--------Branch Manager / Service Manager / Parts Manager  As a Branch Manager my duties were as follows.  Overseen the sale of new equipment, used equipment, warehouse operations, rental operations, dispatching  and all branch functions.  Rental and utilization of our fleet to insure maximum utilization was achieved.  Make sure we complied with all Federal, State, DOT, and OSHA regulations.  Prepare budgets for all departments for the next fiscal year.  Sale of contractor supplies and consumables to the end users .  Staffing our location according to the budget and needed employees for the work load.  Fleet management through our rental and service departments.  Manage 2500 customer accounts directly relating to the branch operations.  Prepare and analyze our monthly P/L statements and deliver them to our District Manager.  Recruit and start the interviewing process of new perspective branch employees.  Overseen the dispatching of 3 delivery trucks and a unionized work force of drivers..  Responsible for all purchasing functions of the branch, and having to sign off on all parts, supplies,  office machinery, and new equipment to insure we stayed in line with our budget numbers.  Meet with vendors to acquire the best pricing for the products we were purchasing.  Meet with municipalities to negotiate bids on equipment, and to insure we were meeting all requested  specifications as required.  Manage warehouse operations from planning and conducting inventories, stocking and location of parts,  return of products, and design for maximum space utilization.  Conduct and prepare employee reviews, training, and make sure employees were adhering to safety policies.  Conduct monthly safety meetings and have employees participate by educating everyone on safe working  procedures.  As a Service Manager my duties were as follows.  Manage all warranty returns to the vendors.  Maintain and order adequate stock to support 8 million dollars of fleet, and 45 different manufacturers.  Manage our inside mechanics, and direct our outside mechanics in service calls, truck stock, and proper  driving procedures through safe driving courses mandated by our company.  Open new work orders, apply the correct parts, mechanics time, and supplies.  Review and close all work orders for processing and generation of invoices.  Insure all equipment has had all PM inspections, and is in safe operating order before the unit could be  considered rental ready.  Coordinate and supervise the overall delivery and performance of our service technicians, and truck  drivers.  Established our service department as a profit center, and a training facility for upcoming service  managers.  Schedule repairs of our equipment, and customer equipment as needed.  Support our sales operations to make sure we were the first call on the customers next purchase.  Maintain records and files for the equipment, both computerized, and a hard copy..  Generate and receive a computerized inventory through the purchase order system.  Maintain a safe productive working environment.  Confer with vendors and coordinate all service related purchases from oil to service trucks.  Do performance reviews on Operating Engineers 513 union employees.  Ensure the department met all financial budgets and goals.  Monitor the condition and inventory of all tools and maintenance equipment. Establish promotional service prices. As a Safety Prfessional- I was concerned when i saw one of your trucks flagging ahead of one of your paving machines on Wildhorse creek road this morning at about 6:40 AM.  There were two workers riding on top of the tool box in back of the cab and only one person actually in the cab.  This practice is dangerous and usually considered illegal.  If tthe truck had to stop suddenly, collided with another vehicle or went off the road the injuries could be very severe.  Just thought someone at your company should knwo this was going on.  It is good that they were warning oncoming traffic of the wide load but the limited sight distance on that road makes these riders even more dangerous than on a more open roadway.
